    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>brioche buns</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and grate the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>mayo</strong> to a small bowl with the <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>grated garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!), 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> of the <strong>pickling</strong> <strong>liquid</strong> from the quick-pickled cucumber<strong> </strong>and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> ranch-style dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
